.TH "rcu_user_exit" 9 "rcu_user_exit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rcu_user_exit \- inform RCU that we are exiting userspace.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void noinstr" rcu_user_exit
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Exit RCU idle mode while entering the kernel because it can
run a RCU read side critical section anytime.

If you add or remove a call to \fBrcu_user_exit\fP, be sure to test with
CONFIG_RCU_EQS_DEBUG=y.
